-- Toyota Guangzhou Plant to Remain Closed Today Because of Supplier Strike
-- Takako Iwatani
-- 2010-06-23T00:07:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/toyota-guangzhou-plant-to-remain-closed-today-because-of-supplier-strike.html

          
          
             Toyota Motor Corp., the world’s
biggest carmaker, said its car factory in Guangzhou, China, will
remain closed today because of a strike at a supplier. The
company hasn’t yet decided whether the plant will operate
tomorrow, Hitoshi Yokoyama, a Beijing-based spokesman for the
Japanese automaker, said today by phone.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
